## Objective
To create a Spring Boot web application using Maven and understand the basic project structure generated by Spring Initializr.

## Tools and Technologies Used
- Java 22
- Spring Boot 3.5.16
- Maven
- IntelliJ IDEA
- Spring Initializr

## Dependencies Used
- Spring Web
- Spring Boot DevTools

## Steps Performed
1. Created a Spring Boot project using Spring Initializr.
2. Selected Maven as the build tool.
3. Added required dependencies.
4. Imported the project into IntelliJ IDEA.
5. Successfully ran the application.


//SpringLearnApplication.java
package com.cognizant.spring_learn;

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;

@SpringBootApplication
public class SpringLearnApplication {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(SpringLearnApplication.class, args);
    }
}

